                           The note contains an ʾAsmat-prayer called sälotä ʾarwe, recited upon people bitten by a snake.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#74ra">Fols. 74ra-75</locus>ra: Ṭǝntä lǝdätomu lä-mänäkosat “Origin of the Monks”. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text is written in a hand similar to the main hand. The last eight lines (fol. 75ra l.3-10), which concern the monks of Tänsǝḥe, were added later in a crude hand.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fols. 1r-2v are made of a fragment of a 16th-cent. (?) Psalter. &#xD;
